SIMPLE: gulp
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gulp
<hw>Gulp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Gulped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gulping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[D. <ets>gulpen</ets>, cf. OD.
<ets>golpe gulf</ets>.]</ety> <def>To swallow eagerly, or in large
draughts; to swallow up; to take down at one swallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He does not swallow, but he <qex>gulps</qex> it down.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The old man . . . glibly <qex>gulped</qex> down the whole
narrative.</q> <rj><qau>Fielding.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To gulp up</b></col>, <cd>to throw up from the stomach;
to disgorge.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gulp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gulp
<hw>Gulp</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of taking a large
mouthful; a swallow, or as much as is awallowed at once.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A disgorging.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gulph</ent>⟦br⟧
